# URL Formatting (Quantastic / External Clips)

The canonical normalization rules for External Clip source URLs are NOT defined in this repo. They live in the shared user-level Cursor skill:

```
~/.cursor/skills/url-formatting/
├── SKILL.md      # workflow + when to apply
├── spec.md       # source of truth — read before changing url-compliance.ts
├── examples.md   # canonical input/output fixtures
└── reference/    # TS reference impl + tests (mirror of this repo)
```

The same spec is shared across:

- **CompiFlow** (this repo) — `src/lib/url-compliance.ts`
- **Quantastic Chrome extension** — for adding clips from the browser
- Any other Quantastic repo that ingests clip URLs

## When changing URL handling

1. Read `~/.cursor/skills/url-formatting/spec.md` first — never derive rules from this repo's code alone.
2. If the rule itself needs to change, update `spec.md` in the skill repo first, then mirror the change here, then update other downstream repos.
3. Tests in `src/lib/url-compliance.test.ts` must stay aligned with `~/.cursor/skills/url-formatting/examples.md`.
4. Issue strings in `url-compliance.ts` are user-facing and must match the spec verbatim (translation happens at the UI layer, not here).
